Text.Value: Leave.

Text.Value: *A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Worms. Crawling under my skin. Get them off, get them off!
Baldur's Gate. The army marches overland, but we've sent some friends ahead to smooth the way.
Nothing of note. Just supplies for the battle ahead - I've already checked it twice over.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
*Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
*As you bear down on his mind, you feel a pulse in response. A thousand pulses, echoing from the nearby crates.*

EditorData.NodeContext: Stiff, awkward, a little wary of us. We're his superior but he thinks we might be a little unstable.

Synopsis: An Absolute guard protecting crates at the dock. The crates contain tadpoles, intended to infect the citizens of Baldur's Gate. The guard doesn't know this, and if we force the knowledge on him his mind breaks.
